  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Resilience To Cope With Climate Change In Urban Areas  (Resccue)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will enable city
managers and urban system operators deciding what the optimal investments would be to cope
with future situations related to hazards in general, and specifically in terms of urban water systems resilience to changing climate. The validation platform is formedby 3 EU cities (Barcelona, Lisboa and Bristol) that
will allow testing the innovative tools developed in the project and
disseminating their results among other cities belonging to major international
networks. In terms of market potential, RESCCUE will generate large potential benefits, in terms of avoided
costs during and after emergencies,
that will contribute to their large-scale
deployment. RESCCUE beneficiaries including local governments, private and public sector institutions, and citizens benefit by having secure, resilient, and consistent water supply through future climate induced critical events.UN Habitat provides through the CRPP engagement both high-level policy advice, and direct technical support.</narrative>
  </description>
